							"description":"Ko'Gornazil marks the first true awakening of a being's inner Flame. Where Ko'Surhul is defined by instinct and unconscious flickers, Ko'Gornazil begins with recognition. Through either the slow accumulation of inexplicable experiences or the direct guidance of a mentor, the soul becomes aware that something deeper stirs within. This awareness births intentionality — even if faint — allowing the bearer to attempt drawing upon their Kori. Yet the process is crude and exhausting. The Flame may surge to answer a desperate call or rise when fear sharpens resolve, but it comes with strain, uncertainty, and a sense of touching something vast with hands too small to hold it.",
